Gabriel Phalane's home in Katlehong was damaged after heavy rains last year. Community leaders have come together to build a new home for the veteran footballer. eTV reporter Pule Letshwiti-Jones has more. Courtesy #DStv403 KATLEHONG - Residents of Katlehong have come together to help one of their soccer heroes. The Phahlane family’s home in the southeast of Johannesburg was damaged after heavy rains last year. Now a new home is being built for them with the help of a civic organisation and the community. The Phahlane family say they’re happy their prayers have finally been answered. * eTV reporter Pule Letshwiti-Jones has more.